<table border='0' width='85%'>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' valign='top' align='left'><font face='Arial' size='2'>With the recent
    changes to pets I decided to take a look at what the buff enhancements for classes
    actually do for pets.  I am looking purely at Level 50 characters, using Level 49
    summoned pets and spells.</font><p><font face='Arial' size='2'>The patch on January 28
    made it so that all pets attack at the same speed regardless of the weapons they wield
    (the exception being Magician pets with inherent differences).  This means that
    unbuffed they have a default attack delay of 30.  The key element now in pet
    supremacy is looking at the buffs which can be given to pets.  </font></p>
    <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>I have received numerous emails from people claiming that
    Enchanters have been seriously weakend by the patch, and even more from Necromancers.
      I decided to draw up some tables of exactly what each class can do to their pets. </font></td>
  </tr>
